                            <comment id="12534367" author="jimk" created="Fri, 12 Oct 2007 19:28:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify the request, what I think you are proposing is adding:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public void put(long lockid, Text column, Writable val)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but you are not proposing to overload any of the get(...) methods or HScannerInterface.next&lt;br/&gt;
to return a Writable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Overloading put is easy. Overloading get and next is hard because we currently do not store any type information for the value. All values are of type byte[]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If that is correct, then yes, we can add this in 0.16.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12534428" author="johanoskarsson" created="Fri, 12 Oct 2007 22:22:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s exactly what I mean. I&apos;ve got a simple patch ready to do that, but can&apos;t submit it until monday. If anyone of you guys want to do one yourselves before then, be my guest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12534899" author="johanoskarsson" created="Mon, 15 Oct 2007 17:13:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mini patch to overload put to allow the user to pass a Writable instead of a byte array.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
